{
  "hook": "Your 3D prints keep failing? Check these 6 mistakes.",
  "headline": "6 Common 3D Printing Mistakes and How to Fix Them",
  "body": [
    "Most print failures come from the same handful of mistakes",
    "Fix these six and watch your success rate soar",
    "Simple adjustments, massive improvement"
  ],
  "insight": "The majority of 3D print failures stem from just a few common mistakes: poor bed leveling, wrong temperatures, thin walls, no supports, wet filament, and excessive speed.",
  "source": "All3DP, Sovol3D, Prusa Research",
  "source_url": "https://all3dp.com/1/common-3d-printing-problems-troubleshooting-3d-printer-issues/",
  "pillar": "education",
  "account": "cu-circuits",
  "hashtags": ["#3DPrinting", "#3DPrintingTips", "#FDM", "#AdditiveManufacturing", "#MakerCommunity", "#CuCircuits", "#Prototyping", "#HardwareTips"],
  "caption": "Your 3D prints keep failing and you cannot figure out why?\n\nIt is almost always one of these six mistakes.\n\nWe run 3D printers daily at Cu Circuits for prototyping enclosures and jigs. After thousands of prints, we have seen every failure mode. And the fix is usually simpler than you think.\n\n1. Skipping bed leveling (the #1 cause of first layer failures)\n2. Wrong temperature for your material\n3. Walls too thin to actually print solid\n4. Printing overhangs without supports\n5. Using filament that absorbed moisture\n6. Printing too fast for your setup\n\nSave this card. Next time a print fails, check these six things first before you blame the printer.\n\nWhat is your most common print failure? Share below.\n\n#3DPrinting #3DPrintingTips #FDM #AdditiveManufacturing #MakerCommunity #CuCircuits #Prototyping #HardwareTips",
  "strategy": {"format": "tip_cards_grid", "visual_approach": "2x3 grid of tip cards with icons, short titles, and one line of advice"},
  "html": "<div style=\"width:1080px; height:1350px; background:#0D0D0D; position:relative; overflow:hidden; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif;\">\n\n  <!-- Top accent line -->\n  <div style=\"position:absolute; top:0; left:0; width:100%; height:4px; background:linear-gradient(90deg, #2E8B57, #B87333, #2E8B57);\"></div>\n\n  <!-- Cu Logo -->\n  <div style=\"position:absolute; top:36px; left:40px; width:64px; height:64px; background:#B87333; display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center; font-size:28px; font-weight:800; color:#0D0D0D; letter-spacing:1px;\">Cu</div>\n\n  <!-- Header -->\n  <div style=\"position:absolute; top:44px; left:130px;\">\n    <div style=\"font-size:14px; color:#2E8B57; font-weight:600; letter-spacing:3px; text-transform:uppercase;\">QUICK FIX GUIDE</div>\n  </div>\n\n  <!-- Title -->\n  <div style=\"position:absolute; top:120px; left:40px; right:40px;\">\n    <div style=\"font-size:46px; font-weight:800; color:#FFFFFF; line-height:1.15; letter-spacing:-1px;\">6 Common 3D Printing<br>Mistakes (and Fixes)</div>\n  </div>\n\n  <!-- 2x3 Grid of Tip Cards -->\n  <div style=\"position:absolute; top:290px; left:40px; right:40px; display:flex; flex-wrap:wrap; gap:20px;\">\n\n    <!-- Card 1: Bed Leveling -->\n    <div style=\"width:480px; background:linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(255,68,68,0.12) 0%, rgba(255,68,68,0.04) 100%); border:1px solid rgba(255,68,68,0.2); border-radius:20px; padding:28px;\">\n      <div style=\"display:flex; align-items:center; gap:14px;\">\n        <div style=\"width:60px; height:60px; background:rgba(255,68,68,0.15); border-radius:14px; display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center; font-size:32px;\">&#128507;</div>\n        <div>\n          <div style=\"font-size:13px; color:#FF4444; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:1px;\">MISTAKE #1</div>\n          <div style=\"font-size:22px; font-weight:800; color:#FFFFFF; margin-top:2px;\">Skipping Bed Leveling</div>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n      <div style=\"margin-top:14px; padding-top:14px; border-top:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.06);\">\n        <div style=\"font-size:15px; color:rgba(255,255,255,0.7); line-height:1.5;\">&#10148; Level before every print. Use a paper sheet test. The nozzle should barely grip the paper at all four corners.</div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Card 2: Wrong Temperature -->\n    <div style=\"width:480px; background:linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(232,160,76,0.12) 0%, rgba(232,160,76,0.04) 100%); border:1px solid rgba(232,160,76,0.2); border-radius:20px; padding:28px;\">\n      <div style=\"display:flex; align-items:center; gap:14px;\">\n        <div style=\"width:60px; height:60px; background:rgba(232,160,76,0.15); border-radius:14px; display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center; font-size:32px;\">&#127777;&#65039;</div>\n        <div>\n          <div style=\"font-size:13px; color:#E8A04C; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:1px;\">MISTAKE #2</div>\n          <div style=\"font-size:22px; font-weight:800; color:#FFFFFF; margin-top:2px;\">Wrong Nozzle Temp</div>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n      <div style=\"margin-top:14px; padding-top:14px; border-top:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.06);\">\n        <div style=\"font-size:15px; color:rgba(255,255,255,0.7); line-height:1.5;\">&#10148; PLA: 190 to 220&deg;C. ABS: 230 to 250&deg;C. PETG: 220 to 250&deg;C. Always match temp to your exact filament brand.</div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Card 3: Thin Walls -->\n    <div style=\"width:480px; background:linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(184,115,51,0.12) 0%, rgba(184,115,51,0.04) 100%); border:1px solid rgba(184,115,51,0.2); border-radius:20px; padding:28px;\">\n      <div style=\"display:flex; align-items:center; gap:14px;\">\n        <div style=\"width:60px; height:60px; background:rgba(184,115,51,0.15); border-radius:14px; display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center; font-size:32px;\">&#128208;</div>\n        <div>\n          <div style=\"font-size:13px; color:#B87333; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:1px;\">MISTAKE #3</div>\n          <div style=\"font-size:22px; font-weight:800; color:#FFFFFF; margin-top:2px;\">Walls Too Thin</div>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n      <div style=\"margin-top:14px; padding-top:14px; border-top:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.06);\">\n        <div style=\"font-size:15px; color:rgba(255,255,255,0.7); line-height:1.5;\">&#10148; Minimum wall thickness should be 2 to 3x your nozzle diameter. For a 0.4mm nozzle, aim for at least 0.8 to 1.2mm walls.</div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Card 4: No Supports -->\n    <div style=\"width:480px; background:linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(46,139,87,0.12) 0%, rgba(46,139,87,0.04) 100%); border:1px solid rgba(46,139,87,0.2); border-radius:20px; padding:28px;\">\n      <div style=\"display:flex; align-items:center; gap:14px;\">\n        <div style=\"width:60px; height:60px; background:rgba(46,139,87,0.15); border-radius:14px; display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center; font-size:32px;\">&#127959;&#65039;</div>\n        <div>\n          <div style=\"font-size:13px; color:#2E8B57; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:1px;\">MISTAKE #4</div>\n          <div style=\"font-size:22px; font-weight:800; color:#FFFFFF; margin-top:2px;\">No Support Structures</div>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n      <div style=\"margin-top:14px; padding-top:14px; border-top:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.06);\">\n        <div style=\"font-size:15px; color:rgba(255,255,255,0.7); line-height:1.5;\">&#10148; Overhangs beyond 45&deg; need supports. Enable tree supports in your slicer for cleaner removal and less scarring.</div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Card 5: Wet Filament -->\n    <div style=\"width:480px; background:linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(100,149,237,0.12) 0%, rgba(100,149,237,0.04) 100%); border:1px solid rgba(100,149,237,0.2); border-radius:20px; padding:28px;\">\n      <div style=\"display:flex; align-items:center; gap:14px;\">\n        <div style=\"width:60px; height:60px; background:rgba(100,149,237,0.15); border-radius:14px; display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center; font-size:32px;\">&#128167;</div>\n        <div>\n          <div style=\"font-size:13px; color:#6495ED; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:1px;\">MISTAKE #5</div>\n          <div style=\"font-size:22px; font-weight:800; color:#FFFFFF; margin-top:2px;\">Wet Filament</div>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n      <div style=\"margin-top:14px; padding-top:14px; border-top:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.06);\">\n        <div style=\"font-size:15px; color:rgba(255,255,255,0.7); line-height:1.5;\">&#10148; Moisture causes bubbling, stringing, and weak layers. Store filament in sealed bags with desiccant. Dry before use if stored open.</div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Card 6: Too Fast -->\n    <div style=\"width:480px; background:linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.08) 0%, rgba(255,255,255,0.02) 100%); border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.12); border-radius:20px; padding:28px;\">\n      <div style=\"display:flex; align-items:center; gap:14px;\">\n        <div style=\"width:60px; height:60px; background:rgba(255,255,255,0.08); border-radius:14px; display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center; font-size:32px;\">&#9889;</div>\n        <div>\n          <div style=\"font-size:13px; color:rgba(255,255,255,0.5); font-weight:700; letter-spacing:1px;\">MISTAKE #6</div>\n          <div style=\"font-size:22px; font-weight:800; color:#FFFFFF; margin-top:2px;\">Printing Too Fast</div>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n      <div style=\"margin-top:14px; padding-top:14px; border-top:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.06);\">\n        <div style=\"font-size:15px; color:rgba(255,255,255,0.7); line-height:1.5;\">&#10148; Speed kills quality. Start at 40 to 60mm/s for detailed parts. Increase only after you nail the basics. Slow and steady wins.</div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n  </div>\n\n  <!-- Footer -->\n  <div style=\"position:absolute; bottom:24px; left:40px; right:40px; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center;\">\n    <div style=\"font-size:14px; color:rgba(255,255,255,0.3); font-weight:600;\">cucircuits.com</div>\n    <div style=\"font-size:12px; color:rgba(255,255,255,0.2);\">Fix these first. Print better forever.</div>\n  </div>\n\n</div>"
}
